Member Enumeration Documentation

enum gaia::storage::ObbStateListener::ObbStateEnum
Enumerator:
OBB_MOUNTED 

The OBB container is now mounted and ready for use.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_UNMOUNTED 

The OBB container is now unmounted and not usable.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_INTERNAL 

There was an internal system error encountered while trying to mount the OBB.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_COULD_NOT_MOUNT 

The OBB could not be mounted by the system.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_COULD_NOT_UNMOUNT 

The OBB could not be unmounted.

This most likely indicates that a file is in use on the OBB. Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_NOT_MOUNTED 

A call was made to unmount the OBB when it was not mounted.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_ALREADY_MOUNTED 

The OBB has already been mounted.

Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager

OBB_ERROR_PERMISSION_DENIED 

The current application does not have permission to use this OBB.

This could be because the OBB indicates it's owned by a different package or some other error. Returned in status messages from calls made via StorageManager
